Introduction

Juri, also known by her full name Takahashi Juri, is a Japanese singer. She was a member of the girl group Rocket Punch and a member of the Japanese supergroup AKB48.

In 2011, Juri joined AKB48 after passing their 12th Generation auditions. She eventually became the captain of Team B.

In 2018, she participated in Mnet's survival show Produce 48. She was eliminated in the finale after ranking 16th place. She competed on the MNET survival show Queendom Puzzle but was eliminated in 12th place.

On March 4, Juri announced during her birthday event that she would be graduating from AKB48 and would be pursuing a career in Korea after signing with Woollim Entertainment. Woollim confirmed the news that same day, stating that she will debut in the agency's upcoming girl group.

On July 22, the agency released a concept film showing the six members of their new girl group, Rocket Punch, for the first time, with Juri being one of them. On July 29, her individual concept film was released. The group's debut mini album, "Pink Punch", was released on August 7, 2019.

On May 24, 2024, it was announced that Takahashi Juri left both Rocket Punch and Woollim Entertainment following the expiration of her contract.

As of late, according to her SNS, she is currently starting her own K-POP and K_Beauty consulting company.
